InferBench — a benchmark for LLMs writing Inferno/InferNode code.

Code in this repository is MIT-licensed (see LICENSE).

Item content is licensed per-item via the `provenance.spdx` field on each
item record. The mix:

  - Items authored fresh for this benchmark: MIT.
  - Items derived/transformed from upstream Inferno (Vita Nuova / Lucent)
    source: declared under the upstream Lucent Public License 1.02 or
    the applicable upstream license, with `provenance.derived_from`
    recording the source path.
  - Items derived from Plan 9 from User Space (`9fans/plan9port`):
    declared MIT (plan9port's license).
  - Items grounded in the Inferno Programmer's Manual: prompt phrasings
    are original; the underlying *concepts* are documented in the IPM.

A per-item license summary is emitted at `LICENSES/MANIFEST.json` by the
CI pipeline.

This benchmark was bootstrapped from prior work on the
`infernode-os-llm` companion repository's `eval/scenarios/baseline_v2.yaml`,
which becomes the `smoke` subset here.
